# Implementation Plan - Mood & Calendar Enhancements

## Goal
Improve mood selection UX (no default), visualize moods on the calendar, and fix text input layout issues.

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Mood Selection (Remove Auto-Default)

#### [MODIFY] [app_colors.dart](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/lib/theme/app_colors.dart)
- Update `MoodColors.getColor(int mood)` to safely handle `mood <= 0` (return a neutral/grey color).

#### [MODIFY] [today_screen.dart](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/lib/screens/today_screen.dart)
- Initialize `_mood = 0` (instead of 3).
- Update [_loadEntryFor](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/lib/screens/today_screen.dart#238-263): If no entry, set `_mood = 0`.
- Update [_buildMoodPage](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/lib/screens/today_screen.dart#324-452):
    - Handle `_mood == 0` case (show placeholder or prompt).
    - Update [_emojiForMood](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/lib/screens/today_screen.dart#264-265) to handle 0.
    - Update [_moodLabel](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/lib/screens/today_screen.dart#265-267) to handle 0.
- Update [_autoSave](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/lib/screens/today_screen.dart#87-132): Save entry even if mood is 0 (user might just want to journal text), but ensure we don't default to 3.

### 2. Stats & Data Handling

#### [MODIFY] [stats_screen.dart](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/lib/screens/stats_screen.dart)
- Update stats calculations (average, best/worst day, distribution) to filter out entries where `mood == 0`.

#### [MODIFY] [store.dart](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/lib/services/store.dart)
- Ensure chart data methods handle/ignore `mood == 0`.

### 3. Calendar Visualization

#### [MODIFY] [calendar_screen.dart](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/lib/screens/calendar_screen.dart)
- Implement `calendarBuilders` in `TableCalendar`.
- `defaultBuilder` & `selectedBuilder` & `todayBuilder`:
    - Check if `store.forDay(day)` exists.
    - If yes and `mood > 0`, return a container with the mood color.
    - If yes and `mood == 0`, maybe show a neutral dot.
    - If no entry, preserve default layout.

### 4. Textbox Formatting

#### [MODIFY] [today_screen.dart](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/lib/screens/today_screen.dart)
- In [_buildFieldPage](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/lib/screens/today_screen.dart#453-649):
    - Adjust `Padding` logic. Use `EdgeInsets.only` with a calculation that accounts for viewInsets simply or uses a spacer.
    - ensure `SingleChildScrollView` allows scrolling to the field when keyboard is up.
    - Add `keyboardDismissBehavior: ScrollViewKeyboardDismissBehavior.onDrag`? No, maybe `manual`.

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
1. **Mood Selection**:
    - Open app (fresh day). Verify "How are you feeling?" shows no selection.
    - Type in text box. Verify entry saves.
    - Go to Calendar. Verify entry exists.
    - Go back to Today. Verify mood is still unselected.
    - Select mood. Verify it updates.
2. **Calendar**:
    - Check past days with entries. Verify they have colored backgrounds matching the mood.
    - Check days without entries. Verify they look normal (text only).
3. **Textbox**:
    - Go to "What went well?".
    - Tap text field. Keyboard opens.
    - Verify layout adjusts smoothly and doesn't "mess up" (header/content shouldn't overlap awkwardly).
4. **Stats**:
    - Verify stats don't crash with mood 0 entries.
